column1: strength for significantly higher thermal conductivity. GRCop-42 achieves 85% of the International Annealed Copper
Standard (IACS) versus 75% IACS for GRCop-84 at room temperature. The alloy was of prime interest for reusable
expander cycle rocket engines such as the proposed RL-60. While the database for GRCop-42 is less extensive than
the one for GRCop-84, sufficient information does exist for directly comparing the two alloys in the extruded form.
